Description: Stanford AI100 is a one hundred year study on artificial intelligence.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Stanford University has invited leading thinkers from several institutions to begin a 100-year effort to study and anticipate how the effects of artificial intelligence will ripple through every aspect of how people work, live and play. This effort, called the One Hundred Year Study on Artificial Intelligence, or AI100, is the brainchild of computer scientist and Stanford alumnus Eric Horvitz who, among other credits, is a former president of the Association for the Advancement of Artificial Intelligence. In that capacity Horvitz convened a conference in 2009 at which top researchers considered advances in artificial intelligence and its influences on people and society, a discussion that illuminated the need for continuing study of AI’s long-term implications. Now, together with Russ Altman, a professor of bioengineering and computer science at Stanford, Horvitz has formed a committee that will select a panel to begin a series of periodic studies on how AI will affect automation, national security, psychology, ethics, law, privacy, democracy and other issues.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Science and Engineering, Software

Description: KMC manufactures a wide range of quality instruments for a variety of military and general aviation aircraft.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Kelly Manufacturing Company is the manufacturer of the R.C. Allen line of instruments. KMC is the largest manufacturer of general aviation aircraft instruments in the world and has two manufacturing plants. One is situated in the downtown area of Wichita, Kansas, and the second is located in Grenola, Kansas. Both plants also operate FAA licensed repair stations. R.C. Allen Inc. was founded by Ralph C. Allen (1884-1967) in 1932, in Grand Rapids, Michigan. Later, it became known as R.C. Allen Business Machines Inc. and was one of the leading manufacturers of business machines. Thousands of old R.C. Allen cash registers, adding machines, and typewriters can still be found across the country today. At the onset of World War II, the need for a large quantity of aircraft propelled R.C. Allen Business Machines into the aviation world. R.C. Allen had the facilities to manufacture the delicate instruments needed for the war effort. Thousands of R.C. Allen Turn and Bank instruments were installed on war-bound aircraft to help win the war for the Allied Forces. After the war, R.C. Allen continued as a major government contractor, and manufactured instruments for the Korean War. Thousands of Rate Gyro Transmitters were made for military jets during this period. During peacetime, the company developed sub-miniature gyros for Saturn rockets, and at one time, twenty of the special gyros were in orbit at the same time. By 1972, R.C. Allen was the largest manufacturer of aircraft instruments for general aviation in the world. In 1977, R.C. Allen Business Machines Inc. was sold off and the instrument division was Kelly Mfgmoved to the AIR CAPITAL OF THE WORLD, Wichita, Kansas. Under new ownership, it became the R.C. Allen Division of Aircraft Instrument and Development (AID). The Kelly Manufacturing Company purchased the company in 1996, becoming the new manufacturer of the R.C. Allen line of flight instruments.  Today, the R.C. Allen brand still retains its position as aviation’s most trusted line of aircraft instruments worldwide. KMC manufactures a wide range of quality instruments for a variety of military and general aviation aircraft. With the introduction of the new RCA 2600 Series Digital Horizon and the new Emergency Standby Power (ESP) battery backup, KMC stays on the cutting edge of aviation technology and safety.

For our member venues (of which there are over 80 at this time), we act as a complete operating system for negotiating and managing parties and events directly with consumers. The site handles everything from initial contact all the way through credit card deposit, email invitation and guest list generation plus several ancillary functions such as event/deal promotion, scheduling calendar and even a marketplace of vendors and services geared towards the nightlife industry. All of this revolves around a micro-payment strategy of $1.00 for every person the site sends through the doors of a member venue.  Currently, the company has undergone one round of funding via friends & family, has fully built and launched the website (www.venugo.com) and has netted over 21,000 visitors. After closely monitoring user transactions and making minor adjustments to the site based on outcomes, the company is currently funding a modest advertising campaign and actively seeking a second tranche of investment capital. For more information or to receive an investor package, email: info@venugo.com

Description: Asher Enterprises provides private investment capital for small businesses and convertible loans for companies.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Curt Kramer founded Asher Enterprises to provide funding to small businesses who either decide not to work with traditional banks or who were denied by traditional banks. The company provides loans to start-ups out of its own assets. In exchange for these loans, we issue convertible promissory notes.  Convertible promissory notes help small businesses manage their cash-flow. Instead of repaying the loan in cash, our company has the right to convert the amount owed to equity in the company. If a small business succeeds, this is a positive situation for all parties.  Curt's Bio Before he started Asher Enterprises, Curt was a successful private investor. He started the company as a way to help other entrepreneurs and go-getters like himself. With his market know-how and skill, Curt has shown that he has what it takes to lead Asher Enterprises into the future. As he is the only shareholder in the company, his decisions are final. Born and raised on Long Island, Curt decided that Great Neck, NY was the ideal place to establish offices for Asher Enterprises. A man committed to both family and community, Curt married his high school girlfriend. Together, they are raising a family of three children. Curt is an employee's boss. An avid reader, he's always ready to share the latest inspiring book with his staff. He's also there to provide a listening ear to employees and to help them advance in their career. Employees rest assured that they can turn to Curt with any concerns. What We Do An avid investor, Curt is able to see the potential for many small businesses, which is why Asher Enterprises is so willing to invest. A community cannot thrive if there is no growth, and that growth comes from new businesses. However, that is not the way the traditional banking industry works. With traditional banking, you have to prove your creditworthiness before you get a loan. With a new start-up business, proving past creditworthiness is nearly impossible, unless you want to risk your own assets. But Asher Enterprises does not rely on credit histories or scores to deliver funding. The ability to make a final decision on a loan comes to down to Curt, not a numerical score. Asher Enterprises is not alone in its desire to lend to small business. Recently, the House of Representatives passed the Jumpstart Our Business Startups Act, which promotes loans for new companies.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The Unimed Massager is a state-of-the-art TENS unit device designed to give you hours of relief and relaxation. Completely safe and easy to use in the privacy of your own space, the Unimed Massager is ideal for those aches and pains we accumulate from daily activities like sports, driving, housework, and even extended periods of sitting. You may have heard the saying, "sitting is the new smoking". The modern lifestyle really does lead us to over-sit. Driving to and from work, sitting in your office chair all day, then coming home and sitting in front of the television_ sound familiar? In this way, many of our muscles go unused while others are over-stretched, causing your posture to slip and body aches and pains to begin.  The Unimed Massager is the ideal TENS unit to counteract this problem; it is lightweight and easily portable, and has a large LCD screen for easy selection of the type and strength of massage you need. Additionally, a rechargeable lithium ion battery, together with our extensive range of compatible accessories, makes the Unimed massager ideal for hours of safe relaxation. Simply attach the electrodes to your pain points as described in the instruction manual, and lay back to relax!  The Unimed Massager arrives in a functional storage box with additional accessories including electrode pads, electrode cables, a battery charger, a USB cable, and an instructional manual.

Description: Manage & share your events as they happen
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Eventnode is a mobile app that customers can use to manage their events (eg. birthday parties, holiday trips etc). Hosts invite their guests & friends to events, and guests respond to the invitations. Hosts can also share their event "as it happens" using an event stream. An event stream consists of photo/videos/text notes. They can share this event stream with only those they invite including those that can't attend the event. Unlike other event based apps, Eventnode focuses on the social nature of events, (i.e., sharing of photos/videos/notes in a story format) than the invitation process. This can be seen in the very nature of the app design. Privacy is another key aspect of the eventnode app. For example: unlike most event management apps, we require all our users to sign up. We believe that restricting the list of people that can view an event to an invitee list will enable users to share the moments that they wouldn’t feel comfortable sharing on a public platform like Facebook.
